Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of folksonomy and clustering analysis to develop a weighted network of tags for knowledge management systems. This topic falls under several sub-categories, including social and information retrieval (cs.SI), digital libraries (cs.DL), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), and possibly system and control (cs.SD) due to the focus on developing a dynamic system. However, since the paper primarily deals with the analysis of user-generated tags and their structure, cs.SI and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories.
